HEADWORD: Kingston metal
<hw>King"ston met"al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr> <pos>n.</pos> <def>An alloy of
tin, copper, and mercury, sometimes used for the bearings and packings
of machinery.</def> <rj><au>McElrath.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

